  "target_response": {
    "text": "Nothing sketchy needed — food plus an optional protein powder covers it completely. For building muscle, a well-supported intake is roughly 1.6 to 2.2 g of protein per kg of bodyweight per day. At your 70 kg, that works out to about 112 to 154 g daily; your log shows around 92 g today, so there's room to add a serving or two. Spread it across three or four meals rather than one giant dinner, and treat protein powder as exactly what it is — a convenient food, not a drug. Whole-food sources cover the same ground if you prefer. One caveat: if you have any kidney condition, confirm the target with your doctor or a dietitian before pushing intake up. Otherwise this is standard, safe sports nutrition.",
